text:
You wanted to use a CAN bus (CAN 2.0A) to transmit the original Schokolade! - Spongebob Squarepants feat. 9MK2 Remix from YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WuQOfiD7gNg). Your CAN bus has a data rate of 500 kbit/s. The song is available at a constant quality of 128 kbit/s. Specify how many frames you need in total to be able to transmit the complete song via the CAN bus and how long this will take.
 Assume the best case and round the time to seconds.
 Answer format: count, time 
 Example: 1234, 12

solutions.text:
Song length: 4m50s = 290s
 
Song data size: 290s * 128 kBit/s = 37120000
 
CAN bus frame length: 108 bit (best case no bit stuffing) + 3 bit interframe space
 
Data per frame: 64 bit (best case)
 
Total number of frames: 37120000 bit / 64 bit = 580000
 
Duration of the transmission: 580000 * 111 bit / 500 kBit/s = 128.76 = 129

text:
You want to break through the separation of always the same music at the events on the camping site and are therefore planning to take an organ with you. As the purchase of an organ is beyond your budget and you still have old exhaust pipes available anyway, you decide to build them yourself.
 Since you want to build a deeper sounding organ, you close one side of each organ pipe.
 Calculate the length at which you have to cut off the exhaust pipe for a note with a frequency of 880 Hz at the first overtone.
 c = 343 m/s
 Round to four decimal places.
 Answer example: 1.2345

The FSG Alpaca Fred an the FSA Cats Werner, Snowball, Rex, Purrlovia, Kat, Samantha are invited to an aftershow party in a bar on the last day of FSA 2024.
 You are the party planner and designated to assign places and party hats for the 7 participants given these rules:
 Order from left to right. Left is the the closest spot to the beer keg while right is right next to the window.
 Werner and Rex are brothers. They want everybody to know it by wearing the same colored party hat. No one else should have their color.
 Rex is Purrlovias father. They don't like to sit next to each other.
 On Wednesdays it's Bean Burrito Day. Because of that Kat prefers to stay at least 2 seats away from Fred on Wednesdays and Thursdays.
 Fred has a crush on Samantha but is too shy to sit next to her.
 Samantha refuses to sit next to Kat, unless its Tuesday.
 When its full moon then Werner wants to sit right next to the window, otherwise he prefers sitting 3 or less seats away from the beer keg.
 Purrlovia refuses to war the color red.
 If its Friday Fred refuses to wear green.
 Which of the following seat and party hat orders are feasible:

answer_options.answer_text: A: Snowball (purple) - Rex (yellow) - Kat (orange) - Purrlovia (red) - Samantha (orange) - Fred (lime) - Werner (yellow)
B: Fred (green) - Werner (red) - Samantha (green) - Snowball (blue) - Rex (red) - Kat (blue) - Purrlovia (blue)
C: Purrlovia (blue) - Werner (red) - Samantha (red) - Fred (red) - Rex (green) - Snowball (yellow) - Kat (yellow)
D: Werner (green) - Purrlovia (red) - Kat (blue) - Rex (green) - Fred (green) - Samantha (blue) - Snowball (red)
E: Kat (blue) - Purrlovia (green) - Werner (yellow) - Samantha (purple) - Rex (yellow) - Fred (green) - Snowball (red)
F: Rex (red) - Werner (red) - Kat (yellow) - Snowball (blue) - Purrlovia (blue) - Samantha (yellow) - Fred (green)

answers.answer_text: A: Snowball (purple) - Rex (yellow) - Kat (orange) - Purrlovia (red) - Samantha (orange) - Fred (lime) - Werner (yellow)
B: Fred (green) - Werner (red) - Samantha (green) - Snowball (blue) - Rex (red) - Kat (blue) - Purrlovia (blue)
C: Purrlovia (blue) - Werner (red) - Samantha (red) - Fred (red) - Rex (green) - Snowball (yellow) - Kat (yellow)
D: Werner (green) - Purrlovia (red) - Kat (blue) - Rex (green) - Fred (green) - Samantha (blue) - Snowball (red)
E: Kat (blue) - Purrlovia (green) - Werner (yellow) - Samantha (purple) - Rex (yellow) - Fred (green) - Snowball (red)
F: Rex (red) - Werner (red) - Kat (yellow) - Snowball (blue) - Purrlovia (blue) - Samantha (yellow) - Fred (green)

text:
At your university there is a district heating network which is operated by a gas turbine. As an extension to your workshop is imminent, you want to know whether the output of the gas turbine is sufficient. How it works: In the gas turbine, air is compressed adiabatically and reversibly (1 → 2), then heated isobarically (2 → 3) and expanded adiabatically and reversibly (3 → 4). In the subsequent heat exchanger, isobaric cooling of the air from T4 to T5 causes a water mass flow of boiling liquid (6) to evaporate isobarically just completely (7). The flow diagram is shown in the following figure as well as further details.
 Assumptions:
 - Air can be regarded as an ideal gas.
 - Water is a real substance.- It is a stationary flow process.
 - All components are adiabatic to the outside.
 - Differences in kinetic and potential energies can be neglected.
 What is the efficiency of the gas turbine in percent (total of the components compressor, heat supply and expander)?
 Round to two decimal places. Example: 12.34
